{"id": "test-00138", "text": "LONDON 1996-12-06", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "LONDON"}]}
{"id": "test-00139", "text": "Result of an English F.A. Challenge", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 13, "end": 35, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "English F.A. Challenge"}]}
{"id": "test-00140", "text": "Cup second round match on Friday:", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 3, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Cup"}]}
{"id": "test-00141", "text": "Plymouth 4 Exeter 1", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 8, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Plymouth"}, {"start": 11, "end": 17, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Exeter"}]}
{"id": "test-00142", "text": "SOCCER - BLINKER BAN LIFTED.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 9, "end": 16, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "BLINKER"}]}
{"id": "test-00143", "text": "LONDON 1996-12-06", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "LONDON"}]}
{"id": "test-00144", "text": "Dutch forward Reggie Blinker had his indefinite suspension lifted by FIFA on Friday and was set to make his Sheffield Wednesday comeback against Liverpool on Saturday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Dutch"}, {"start": 14, "end": 28, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Reggie Blinker"}, {"start": 69, "end": 73, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "FIFA"}, {"start": 108, "end": 127, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Sheffield Wednesday"}, {"start": 145, "end": 154, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Liverpool"}]}
{"id": "test-00145", "text": "Blinker missed his club's last two games after FIFA slapped a worldwide ban on him for appearing to sign contracts for both Wednesday and Udinese while he was playing for Feyenoord.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 7, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Blinker"}, {"start": 47, "end": 51, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "FIFA"}, {"start": 124, "end": 133, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Wednesday"}, {"start": 138, "end": 145, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Udinese"}, {"start": 171, "end": 180, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Feyenoord"}]}
{"id": "test-00146", "text": "FIFA's players' status committee, meeting in Barcelona, decided that although the Udinese document was basically valid, it could not be legally protected.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 4, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "FIFA"}, {"start": 45, "end": 54, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Barcelona"}, {"start": 82, "end": 89, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Udinese"}]}
{"id": "test-00147", "text": "The committee said the Italian club had violated regulations by failing to inform Feyenoord, with whom the player was under contract.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 23, "end": 30, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Italian"}, {"start": 82, "end": 91, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Feyenoord"}]}
{"id": "test-00148", "text": "Blinker was fined 75,000 Swiss francs ($57,600) for failing to inform the Engllsh club of his previous commitment to Udinese.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 7, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Blinker"}, {"start": 25, "end": 30, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Swiss"}, {"start": 74, "end": 81, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Engllsh"}, {"start": 117, "end": 124, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Udinese"}]}
{"id": "test-00149", "text": "SOCCER - LEEDS' BOWYER FINED FOR PART IN FAST-FOOD FRACAS.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 9, "end": 14, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "LEEDS"}, {"start": 16, "end": 22, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "BOWYER"}]}
{"id": "test-00150", "text": "LONDON 1996-12-06", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "LONDON"}]}
{"id": "test-00151", "text": "Leeds' England under-21 striker Lee Bowyer was fined 4,500 pounds ($7,400) on Friday for hurling chairs at restaurant staff during a disturbance at a McDonald's fast-food restaurant.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Leeds"}, {"start": 7, "end": 14, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "England"}, {"start": 32, "end": 42, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Lee Bowyer"}, {"start": 150, "end": 160, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "McDonald's"}]}
{"id": "test-00152", "text": "Bowyer, 19, who was caught in the act by security cameras, pleaded guilty to a charge of affray at a court in London.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Bowyer"}, {"start": 110, "end": 116, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "London"}]}
{"id": "test-00153", "text": "He was fined and ordered to pay a total of 175 pounds to two members of staff injured in the fracas in an east London restaurant in October.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 111, "end": 117, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "London"}]}
{"id": "test-00154", "text": "Leeds had already fined Bowyer 4,000 pounds ($6,600) and warned him a repeat of his criminal behaviour could cost him his place in the side.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Leeds"}, {"start": 24, "end": 30, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Bowyer"}]}
{"id": "test-00155", "text": "Bowyer, who moved to the Yorkshire club in August for 3.5 million pounds ($5.8 million), was expected to play against Middlesbrough on Saturday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Bowyer"}, {"start": 25, "end": 34, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Yorkshire"}, {"start": 118, "end": 131, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Middlesbrough"}]}
